  "text": "Pancreatic CSCs are considered to be a special population of cells with characteristic cell surface expression profile discovered in a plethora of human pancreatic malignancies, which are able to renew themselves infinitely, making multilineage differentiation and resisting to electromagnetic and chemical insults. The most accepted pancreatic CSC markers were CD133, CD44, CD24, CXCR4 and ALDH1 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . As reported, pancreatic CD133",
